The paper discusses the need for interpretable explanations of predictive models, which is a common theme in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also presents a novel algorithm for visualizing statistical interaction effects, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the lack of utilities available for analytical needs, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
